# Task Queue — {{PROJECT_NAME}} (pending)

> The **pending backlog** (⏳ only). The **planning session is the sole assigner** — workers never add
> or reassign tasks here. Each task carries an **`owner`** (who it's assigned to) so resume is
> **assignment-based, not greedy**. One task = one entry with a stable `#N` ID (never renumber). Each task is framed as a
> **goal** — a *verifiable* done-condition (the worker's success criterion; also the optional native `/goal` condition).
>
> **Owner format** — `owner: <handle> · session: <uuid>` (unassigned ⇒ `owner: unassigned`). `<handle>` = a
> stable worker name the planner divvies by (e.g. `worker-2`, or a slice like `renderer`/`data`), durable across
> that worker's re-compacts; `<session>` = that worker's live `$CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` (run `echo "$CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID"`, paste literally — never guess), the exact key the resume hook matches.
> Sessions are stood up first; the planner reads their ids and binds them at assign time.
>
> Lifecycle (the file IS the state — VAN-CLIEF §9): a task lives here while ⏳ pending → **the planner**
> (sole writer of `planning/*.md`) moves it into `progress.md` (🔄) at dispatch → on merge, into
> `memory/completed-tasks.md` (✅). Workers never edit these files — they read their assignment + report in their output. The post-compact resume hook surfaces the next item whose `session:`
> matches THIS session's id; if none is assigned to it, the session **stops and asks** (never grabs another's).

